# Weapon Only Reactions
Bleed	ASPECT:TYPE|Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionWeaponOnly
	DESC:A deep gash sends blood spewing from the wound, a loss soon felt by the opponent unless the bleeding can be stopped.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any attack roll using a weapon with the Bleed reaction.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: At the start of the next series, the opponent takes 1 point of normal damage.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent cannot recover a ny damage until it undergoes a successful Heal or Recover option (no base options can be substituted) and takes another point of lethal damage at the start of every series until the bleeding stops.
	DESC:&nl; Weapon: You must use a weapon with the Bleed reaction.
Burn	ASPECT:TYPE|Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionWeaponOnly
	DESC:The result of an explosive weapon, the opponent or a targeted object catches fire and threatens to become completely engulfed.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any attack roll using a weapon with the Burn reaction.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: The opponent takes a half penalty to all Sense or Mind focus dice as the flames lick across her face and block her vision or inflict too much pain for the opponent to concentrate. Objects simply catch fire.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent automatically takes 1 point of lethal damage at the start of every series until a number of hits are gained by any appropriate active roll vs. Normal difficulty made to put the fire out. Objects lose 1 point of Armor Rating per series and are destroyed at the start of the next series when their Rating is reduced to 0.
	DESC:&nl; Weapon: You must use a weapon with the Burn reaction.
Explode	ASPECT:TYPE|Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionWeaponOnly
	DESC:&nl; Savage weaponry unleashes the explosive potential of nearby objects (or an opponent), causing an immediate fireball threatening to kill anyone in range. This reaction creates an additional burst attack against everyone within 1 Move option of the affected object or opponent.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any burst attack using a weapon with the Explode reaction.
	DESC:&nl; Level: Expert
	DESC:&nl; Weapon: You must use a weapon with the Explode reaction.
Fracture	ASPECT:TYPE|Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionWeaponOnly
	DESC:&nl; A brutal and deliberate hit snaps precious bonus in your opponent and renders the injured area useless for the remainder of the scene (or longer). The opponent suffers a half penalty to all Body focus dice until the injury has been treated with a Heal or Recover option (no base options allowed) with a number of hits equal to the amount of damage inflicted.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any melee attack roll using a weapon with the Fracture reaction.
	DESC:&nl; Level: Expert
	DESC:&nl; Weapon: You must use a weapon with the Fracture reaction.
Slow	ASPECT:TYPE|Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionWeaponOnly
	DESC:&nl; Old-school weapons have a nasty habit of leaving a piece of metal or wooden shaft in an opponent's leg and keeps them from getting away easily.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any attack roll using a weapon with the Slow reaction.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: When afflicted with this reaction, the opponent cannot move any distance when they first use a Move option in a series. Only once a second Move option has been spent can the opponent start to cover any distance.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent can only move up to 1 Move option away by making a stunt roll.
	DESC:&nl; Weapon: You must use a weapon with the Slow reaction.
Untraceable	ASPECT:TYPE|Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionWeaponOnly
	DESC:&nl; Some weapons, particular revolvers, are constructed to avoid leaving shell casings behind.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any attack roll using a weapon with the Untraceable reaction.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: When you roll a natural 1 on your base or focus dice while attacking with such a weapon, you do not gain an Evidence Point. (Your Director will know more about these points.)
	DESC:&nl; Expert: Decrease your total Evidence Points by 1. This reaction can only be applied once per scene.
	DESC:&nl; Weapon: You must use a weapon with the Untraceable reaction.

# Trained Reactions
Confuse	ASPECT:TYPE|Trained (2 points)	COST:2	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionTrained
	DESC:Mastery of language comes in handy from time to time when manipulating lesser students like yourself. See what I did there? That momentary pause gives a sly person the opening they need to slip in a suggestive comment or a concealed phrase.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any active Mind roll. You must have a common form of communication (i.e. language) between yourself and the opponent or take a half penalty to your own Mind focus dice.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: If the opposed Mind roll ties your active roll, you are successful.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent takes a half penalty to all Sense or Mind focus dice until they succeed on any roll with those dice.
	DESC:&nl; Trained: You must have spent training points to gain this reaction.
Daze	ASPECT:TYPE|Trained (3 points)	COST:3	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionTrained
	DESC:&nl; A shot to the head or a jab to the ribs causes the opponent to become woozy and disoriented for a brief moment.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any attack roll.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: Until the opponent recovers at least 1 point of damage or gains a boost, he takes a half penalty to all Body, Sense, and Mind focus dice.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent gains an additional hit penalty to all rolls, even if she's never taken damage, until the end of the scene.
	DESC:&nl; Trained: You must have spent training points to gain this reaction.
Disarm	ASPECT:TYPE|Trained (4 points)	COST:4	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionTrained
	DESC:&nl; Weapons complicate close combat and some thugs need to be disarmed or the mark needs to drop an item their holding before you can drop a grenade down their pants.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any melee or ranged attack roll or an active Body roll against an adjacent opponent. When you spend training points to gain this reaction, you must choose which type of attack applies.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: A solid blow causes the item or weapon to slip loose in the opponent's hand(s). The opponent cannot use a gear's circumstance dice or a weapon's bonus hits in their defense rolls until they regain the Edge.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent drops an item or weapon of your choice from their hands and must use a Quick option to pick it up again.
	DESC:&nl; Trained: You must have spent training points to gain this reaction.
Pocket Item	ASPECT:TYPE|Trained (2 points)	COST:2	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionTrained
	DESC:&nl; Close contact with an opponent puts you in the perfect position to slip a hand inside a pocket, backpack, or other personal possession and slip out an item or place an item in as long as its no larger than your hand. Applying this reaction negates any potential opposed roll to the effort, but you cannot choose the item you're stealing without facing additional difficulty dice to the effort.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any active Body or Sense roll against an adjacent opponent. The pocketed object must have a Weight of 1 or less; heavier objects require 2 hits per extra Weight of the object. If not enough hits are rolled, the reaction fails and the opponent steals the Edge.
	DESC:&nl; Level: Enhanced
	DESC:&nl; Trained: You must have spent training points to gain this reaction.
Stun	ASPECT:TYPE|Trained (5 points)	COST:5	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.ReactionTrained
	DESC:&nl; The attack strikes your opponent along a nerve or joint, causing him to stutter and stumble for a while.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any attack roll.
	DESC:&nl; Level: This reaction works for both Enhanced and Expert reactions.
	DESC:&nl; Enhanced: Once until the end of the current series, you can steal the Edge from the opponent's Team. This can only be done when the stunned opponent prepares to use an option.
	DESC:&nl; Expert: The opponent cannot gain the Edge until the start of the next series.
	DESC:&nl; Trained: You must have spent training points to gain this reaction.



