	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any dice roll against an adjacent opponent.
Pass	ASPECT:TYPE|Base	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.AutoReaction
	DESC:&nl; Beyond simple co-operation between Teammates, the Pass reaction applied to a successful active roll allows you to gang up on an opponent or against difficulty dice. Choose a Teammate; this reaction grants them your bonus option with +1d10. If the Teammate succeeds and gains a bonus option, they can continue to use it for themselves or pass it back to you, but the additional circumstance die only applies to the first roll. If this reaction is gained from a successful opposed or defense roll, you can allow a Teammate to use an automatic option only. In no way shape or form does your Team steal the Edge without the proper number of hits.
	DESC:&nl; Additional Training: Requires 2 additional training points|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Training Pool,Pass Additional
	DESC:&nl; Additional Training: If the Teammate accepting this reaction has spent an additional 2 training points, they can maintain the +1d10 for an additional roll.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Training Pool,Pass Additional
	DESC:&nl; Base Reaction: This reaction is available to everyone in Killshot.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any dice roll.
Push	ASPECT:TYPE|Base	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.AutoReaction
	DESC:&nl; You drive a massive amount of force into your attack and pummel the opponent backwards. The opponent is no longer adjacent and must use a Move or similar option to become adjacent again.
	DESC:&nl; Additional Training: Requires 2 additional training points|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Training Pool,Push Additional
	DESC:&nl; Additional Training: You can apply this reaction with a ranged attack against distant opponents.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Training Pool,Push Additional
	DESC:&nl; Base Reaction: This reaction is available to everyone in Killshot.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any dice roll against an adjacent opponent.
Trip	ASPECT:TYPE|Base	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Reaction.SpecialQuality.AutoReaction
	DESC:&nl; Your attack drops your opponent to the ground. Your opponent must use a Move option to stand back up and suffers a half penalty to all Body focus dice until they do so.
	DESC:&nl; Base Reaction: This reaction is available to everyone in Killshot.
	DESC:&nl; Condition: Any dice roll against an adjacent opponent.
